Barr May Take Republican Votes
Former Republican congressman Bob Barr of Georgia was nominated as the
Libertarian Party's presidential candidate and may take votes away from
John McCain. What do you think?
Young Woman
Linda Vega,
Systems Analyst
"And then there's Barack Obama. That guy's taking a huge chunk of the
vote away from McCain."
Young Man
Alan Chambers,
Welder
"I'd gladly vote for Mr. Barr if I didn't consider the voter
registration process such a flagrant affront of my personal liberties."
Black Man
Andrew Saunders,
Animal Trainer
"So up until this nomination, our best choice to ensure public rights
and personal freedoms was John McCain?"
